<div class="outer-layout-container">

<main class="layout-content layout-container" >

  
  


      <div class="layout-content-full">
      <div>
    <div data-drupal-messages-fallback class="hidden"></div>

  </div>

    </div>  
    
  <div class="layout-container--grid layout-container--has-left-rail layout-container--has-right-rail retain-ltr-area-order">
    <div class="layout-content-main">
        <div>
    <div id="block-pt-content" class="block">
  
    
      

<!-- is_first_page: 1 -->
<!-- recent_posts_offset: 0 -->
<!-- recent_posts_items_per_page: 10 -->
<!-- recent_posts: 1 -->
  <!-- recent_posts_argument: 5019517+5018746+5018400+5017782 -->
  <!-- recent_posts_argument: 54052 -->
<article data-history-node-id="54052" role="article" class="basics-full">
  <div class="content-header d-flex reference-header">
              <div class="content-header--image">
        
            <article>
  
      
              <img src="https://cdn2.psychologytoday.com/assets/styles/manual_crop_1_1_75x75/public/2020-09/shutterstock_1521057026%20%281%29.jpg?itok=MDqayIXH" width="75" height="75" alt="Pixel-Shot/Shutterstock" title="Pixel-Shot/Shutterstock" loading="lazy" />



      
  </article>

      
      </div>
    
    <div class="content-header--text">
                    <h1 class="reference__title section-title">Attention</h1>
                          <p class="content-header--synonyms text-teaser-byline">Distraction</p>
      
                    <p class="reference__review-info fine-print">
          <a href="/us/docs/editorial-process" class="reference__review-info-link">
            <span class="reference__review-info-icon"></span>
            <span class="reference__review-info-text">Reviewed by Psychology Today Staff</span>
          </a>
        </p>
          </div>
  </div>

  <div>
                                              
              <div class="reference__body">
        
<div class="field-name-body">
                    <p>The ability to pay attention to important things&mdash;and ignore the rest&mdash;has been a crucial survival skill throughout human history. Attention can help us focus our awareness on a particular aspect of our environment, important decisions, or the thoughts in our head. Maintaining focus is a perennial challenge for individuals of all ages, and people have long sought out strategies, tricks, and medications to help them stay on track.</p>
            </div>

      </div>
    
          
      <div class="table-of-contents border-top">
        <h4 class="table-of-contents--title">Contents</h4>
        <ul>
                      <li class="table-of-contents--item">
              <a href="#why-attention-matters">
                Why Attention Matters
              </a>
            </li>
                      <li class="table-of-contents--item">
              <a href="#how-to-focus">
                How to Focus
              </a>
            </li>
                      <li class="table-of-contents--item">
              <a href="#when-the-mind-wanders">
                When the Mind Wanders
              </a>
            </li>
                      <li class="table-of-contents--item">
              <a href="#living-with-adhd">
                Living with ADHD
              </a>
            </li>
                  </ul>
      </div>
    
                
          <div class="reference__sections">
        <div>
      <div>  <div class="section section--separator">
          <div id="why-attention-matters" class="section-anchor skip-inline-link-filter"></div>
                      <div class="h2 section-title">
            Why Attention Matters
      </div>
        <div class="section__body">
                      
            <article>
  
      
              <img src="https://cdn2.psychologytoday.com/assets/styles/manual_crop_1_1_180x180/public/2020-09/shutterstock_691385530.jpg?itok=WXiMqznw" width="180" height="180" alt="MemoriesStocker/Shutterstock" title="MemoriesStocker/Shutterstock" loading="lazy" />



      
  </article>

      
                    
            <p>Attention helps us learn in school, get ahead in the workplace, and build successful relationships, but when it's compromised, achievement of any kind becomes far more challenging. Some individuals may seem naturally to have more control over their focus, but most people&rsquo;s ability to pay attention varies depending on the situation, the number of distractions they face, and whether they are employing the aid of stimulants like caffeine or <a href="https://www.psychologytoday.com/us/basics/adhd">Ritalin</a>. And others&mdash;particularly those with <a href="https://www.psychologytoday.com/us/basics/adhd" title="Psychology Today looks at ADHD" class="basics-link" hreflang="en-US">ADHD</a> or other mental health concerns&mdash;may struggle to pay attention even when it matters most.</p>
      
        </div>
          
          
<div class="faqs">
                                                            <div class="faq faq--1">
                <div itemscope  itemprop="mainEntity" itemtype="https://schema.org/Question">
          <div class="faq--title d-flex">
        <div itemprop="name" class="h3 faq--question">
          
            Do some people have shorter attention spans?
      
        </div>
        <div class="faq--control-container">
          <button class="faq--control">
            <div class="faq--control-icon">
              <svg width="13px" height="8px" viewBox="0 0 13 8" version="1.1"
     xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
     xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">
                <!-- Generator: Sketch 46.2 (44496) - http://www.bohemiancoding.com/sketch -->
                <desc>Created with Sketch.</desc>
                <defs></defs>
                <g id="-small" stroke="none" stroke-width="1" fill="none" fill-rule="evenodd">
                  <g id="Tests---Listing-Page---SM"
                     transform="translate(-490.000000, -597.000000)" fill="#2C2D30">
                    <g id="Left-col" transform="translate(74.000000, 162.000000)">
                      <g id="Table" transform="translate(0.000000, 426.000000)">
                        <polygon id="navigatedown"
                                 points="422.310547 16.3125 428.621094 10.0019531 427.62793 9 422.310547 14.3173828 416.993164 9 416 10.0019531"></polygon>
                      </g>
                    </g>
                  </g>
                </g>
              </svg>
            </div>
          </button>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div itemscope="" itemprop="acceptedAnswer" itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer" class="faq--answer">
        <div itemprop="text">
          
            <p>The ability to focus on a particular task for an extended period of time can vary widely among individuals. Evolutionary psychologists speculate that <a href="https://www.psychologytoday.com/us/blog/finding-purpose/201811/when-your-unmotivated-teenager-fails-find-purpose-in-life">individuals with long and short attention spans both had value</a> in early human societies. The latter, for example, might have been novelty-seekers, more adventurous and quicker to migrate than others.</p>
      
        </div>
      </div>
      </div>

            </div>
                                                                <div class="faq faq--2">
                <div itemscope  itemprop="mainEntity" itemtype="https://schema.org/Question">
          <div class="faq--title d-flex">
        <div itemprop="name" class="h3 faq--question">
          
            Is it possible to multitask?
      
        </div>
        <div class="faq--control-container">
          <button class="faq--control">
            <div class="faq--control-icon">
              <svg width="13px" height="8px" viewBox="0 0 13 8" version="1.1"
     xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
     xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">
                <!-- Generator: Sketch 46.2 (44496) - http://www.bohemiancoding.com/sketch -->
                <desc>Created with Sketch.</desc>
                <defs></defs>
                <g id="-small" stroke="none" stroke-width="1" fill="none" fill-rule="evenodd">
                  <g id="Tests---Listing-Page---SM"
                     transform="translate(-490.000000, -597.000000)" fill="#2C2D30">
                    <g id="Left-col" transform="translate(74.000000, 162.000000)">
                      <g id="Table" transform="translate(0.000000, 426.000000)">
                        <polygon id="navigatedown"
                                 points="422.310547 16.3125 428.621094 10.0019531 427.62793 9 422.310547 14.3173828 416.993164 9 416 10.0019531"></polygon>
                      </g>
                    </g>
                  </g>
                </g>
              </svg>
            </div>
          </button>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div itemscope="" itemprop="acceptedAnswer" itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer" class="faq--answer">
        <div itemprop="text">
          
            <p>Many people attempt to perform two or more tasks at once&mdash;driving while texting, for example, or reading while listening to a podcast&mdash;but a growing body of research finds that attempting to split our focus actually leads to <a href="https://www.psychologytoday.com/us/blog/the-squeaky-wheel/201606/10-real-risks-multitasking-mind-and-body">lower efficiency on both tasks</a>, greater <a href="https://www.psychologytoday.com/us/basics/stress" title="Psychology Today looks at stress" class="basics-link" hreflang="en-US">stress</a> and distractibility, and even reductions in the brain&rsquo;s grey matter.</p>
      
        </div>
      </div>
      </div>

            </div>
                                                                <div class="faq faq--3 collapsed">
                <div itemscope  itemprop="mainEntity" itemtype="https://schema.org/Question">
          <div class="faq--title d-flex">
        <div itemprop="name" class="h3 faq--question">
          
            How does sleep affect attention?
      
        </div>
        <div class="faq--control-container">
          <button class="faq--control">
            <div class="faq--control-icon">
              <svg width="13px" height="8px" viewBox="0 0 13 8" version="1.1"
     xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
     xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">
                <!-- Generator: Sketch 46.2 (44496) - http://www.bohemiancoding.com/sketch -->
                <desc>Created with Sketch.</desc>
                <defs></defs>
                <g id="-small" stroke="none" stroke-width="1" fill="none" fill-rule="evenodd">
                  <g id="Tests---Listing-Page---SM"
                     transform="translate(-490.000000, -597.000000)" fill="#2C2D30">
                    <g id="Left-col" transform="translate(74.000000, 162.000000)">
                      <g id="Table" transform="translate(0.000000, 426.000000)">
                        <polygon id="navigatedown"
                                 points="422.310547 16.3125 428.621094 10.0019531 427.62793 9 422.310547 14.3173828 416.993164 9 416 10.0019531"></polygon>
                      </g>
                    </g>
                  </g>
                </g>
              </svg>
            </div>
          </button>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div itemscope="" itemprop="acceptedAnswer" itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer" class="faq--answer">
        <div itemprop="text">
          
            <p>A key to maintaining focus is the ability to recover attention quickly after a distraction. Research shows that people who get less sleep find it <a href="https://www.psychologytoday.com/us/blog/sleep-newzzz/201903/how-your-sleep-can-impact-distraction-levels">much more difficult to rebound from distraction</a>, to complete tasks, and to finish jobs without mistakes. And in the case of driving, when focus is absolutely essential, insufficient rest leads to a higher accident rate.</p>
      
        </div>
      </div>
      </div>

            </div>
                                                                <div class="faq faq--4 collapsed">
                <div itemscope  itemprop="mainEntity" itemtype="https://schema.org/Question">
          <div class="faq--title d-flex">
        <div itemprop="name" class="h3 faq--question">
          
            Why do I sometimes feel time speeding up or slowing down?
      
        </div>
        <div class="faq--control-container">
          <button class="faq--control">
            <div class="faq--control-icon">
              <svg width="13px" height="8px" viewBox="0 0 13 8" version="1.1"
     xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
     xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">
                <!-- Generator: Sketch 46.2 (44496) - http://www.bohemiancoding.com/sketch -->
                <desc>Created with Sketch.</desc>
                <defs></defs>
                <g id="-small" stroke="none" stroke-width="1" fill="none" fill-rule="evenodd">
                  <g id="Tests---Listing-Page---SM"
                     transform="translate(-490.000000, -597.000000)" fill="#2C2D30">
                    <g id="Left-col" transform="translate(74.000000, 162.000000)">
                      <g id="Table" transform="translate(0.000000, 426.000000)">
                        <polygon id="navigatedown"
                                 points="422.310547 16.3125 428.621094 10.0019531 427.62793 9 422.310547 14.3173828 416.993164 9 416 10.0019531"></polygon>
                      </g>
                    </g>
                  </g>
                </g>
              </svg>
            </div>
          </button>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div itemscope="" itemprop="acceptedAnswer" itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer" class="faq--answer">
        <div itemprop="text">
          
            <p>Older individuals tend to experience time as passing more quickly, as do those who find their days to be monotonous or wasted. And research on the so-called <a href="https://www.psychologytoday.com/us/blog/sense-time/201707/the-matrix-effect-when-time-slows-down">&ldquo;Matrix effect&rdquo;</a> has found that, in moments of extreme danger, such as a near accident, our perception of time slows significantly, enabling us to remember moment-by-moment details we cannot produce for more mundane events.</p>
      
        </div>
      </div>
      </div>

            </div>
                                                                <div class="faq faq--5 collapsed faq--last">
                <div itemscope  itemprop="mainEntity" itemtype="https://schema.org/Question">
          <div class="faq--title d-flex">
        <div itemprop="name" class="h3 faq--question">
          
            Can your own mind distract you?
      
        </div>
        <div class="faq--control-container">
          <button class="faq--control">
            <div class="faq--control-icon">
              <svg width="13px" height="8px" viewBox="0 0 13 8" version="1.1"
     xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
     xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">
                <!-- Generator: Sketch 46.2 (44496) - http://www.bohemiancoding.com/sketch -->
                <desc>Created with Sketch.</desc>
                <defs></defs>
                <g id="-small" stroke="none" stroke-width="1" fill="none" fill-rule="evenodd">
                  <g id="Tests---Listing-Page---SM"
                     transform="translate(-490.000000, -597.000000)" fill="#2C2D30">
                    <g id="Left-col" transform="translate(74.000000, 162.000000)">
                      <g id="Table" transform="translate(0.000000, 426.000000)">
                        <polygon id="navigatedown"
                                 points="422.310547 16.3125 428.621094 10.0019531 427.62793 9 422.310547 14.3173828 416.993164 9 416 10.0019531"></polygon>
                      </g>
                    </g>
                  </g>
                </g>
              </svg>
            </div>
          </button>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div itemscope="" itemprop="acceptedAnswer" itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer" class="faq--answer">
        <div itemprop="text">
          
            <p>It&rsquo;s not unusual for our focus to stray, especially when we&rsquo;re consumed by stress or when the task is routine. Many people, for example, have found themselves in their driveway without remembering anything about their trip home. When we are <a href="https://www.psychologytoday.com/us/blog/toward-less-egoic-world/201707/distracted-life">preoccupied by our inner thoughts and self-talk</a>, though, the costs can sometimes be tragic, such as leaving a child unoccupied in a car.</p>
      
        </div>
      </div>
      </div>

            </div>
                        </div>

    
        
  </div>
</div>
          <div class="pt-ad pt-ad--300x250 d-block d-none d-md-block d-lg-none block" id="block-ad-subpage-300x250-programmatically-rendered">
  
    
      <div class="pt-ad--container pt-ad-show-text">
      <div class="pt-ad--text">
      <span>article continues after advertisement</span>
    </div>
