          <div class="teaser--card-inset-details--row">
    

<article class="teaser--card-inset-details blog_entry--teaser--card-inset-details" data-nid="5018400">

      <div class="card-inset-details__image">
      
              <a href="/us/blog/illusions-delusions-and-reality/202403/the-necessity-of-multitasking"><img loading="lazy" src="https://cdn2.psychologytoday.com/assets/styles/manual_crop_3_2_600x400/public/teaser_image/blog_entry/2024-03/shutterstock_1193280682.jpg?itok=hqcmYTMS" width="600" height="400" alt="" title="Artie Medvedev/Shutterstock" />

</a>

      
    </div>
  
  <div class="card-inset-details__body">

          <div class="card-inset-details__title">
        <a href="/us/blog/illusions-delusions-and-reality/202403/the-necessity-of-multitasking" title="The Necessity of Multitasking"> The Necessity of Multitasking </a>
      </div>
    
          <div class="card-inset-details__teaser-text">
        
            Decades of research have pointed out the costs associated with multitasking. But in many daily contexts, multitasking may be the most efficient thing to do.
      
      </div>
    
  </div>

</article>


  
    

<article class="teaser--card-inset-details blog_entry--teaser--card-inset-details" data-nid="5017782">

      <div class="card-inset-details__image">
      
              <a href="/us/blog/the-art-of-self-improvement/202403/your-attention-please"><img loading="lazy" src="https://cdn2.psychologytoday.com/assets/styles/manual_crop_3_2_600x400/public/teaser_image/blog_entry/2024-03/niklas-hamann-Pe4gh8a8mBY-unsplash.jpg?itok=XVRDS4ji" width="600" height="400" alt="" title="Niklas Hamann / Unsplash" />

</a>

      
    </div>
  
  <div class="card-inset-details__body">

          <div class="card-inset-details__title">
        <a href="/us/blog/the-art-of-self-improvement/202403/your-attention-please" title="Your Attention, Please!"> Your Attention, Please! </a>
      </div>
    
          <div class="card-inset-details__teaser-text">
        
            Damaging myths about attention keep us from cognitive thriving. We have much to gain if we change our perspective and treat attention as a precious and limited resource.
      
      </div>
    
  </div>

</article>      </div>
    


  </section>

    

  
  

  
  
</div>
